 Position: DevOps Engineer
📍 Location: Islamabad, Pakistan
🏢 Company: CloudNest Solutions
💼 Type: Full-Time | On-site/Hybrid
📅 Experience Level: Mid-Level (2–4 years)

🔧 About the Role
CloudNest Solutions is looking for a skilled DevOps Engineer to streamline and automate our software delivery pipeline. You’ll work closely with development, QA, and infrastructure teams to ensure smooth CI/CD processes, cloud operations, and infrastructure scalability.

💡 What You’ll Do
Design, implement, and maintain CI/CD pipelines (GitHub Actions, Jenkins, GitLab CI, etc.)

Manage and provision cloud infrastructure using tools like Terraform or AWS CloudFormation

Monitor and maintain high availability of systems through observability tools (Prometheus, Grafana, ELK)

Automate repetitive tasks using scripting (Bash, Python)

Manage containerization and orchestration (Docker, Kubernetes, ECS)

Enforce best practices for infrastructure security, scalability, and compliance

Work on incident management, root cause analysis, and system optimization

Collaborate with developers and QA engineers to support the full development lifecycle

✅ Requirements
Bachelor’s in Computer Science, IT, or related field

2–4 years of hands-on DevOps experience

Strong understanding of Linux-based infrastructure

Experience with cloud platforms (AWS is a must; Azure/GCP is a plus)

Proficient in Docker, Kubernetes, and Helm

Familiar with Terraform, Ansible, or other IaC tools

Knowledge of monitoring/logging tools like Prometheus, ELK, CloudWatch

Strong scripting skills in Bash, Python, or similar

🌟 Nice to Have
Experience in security compliance and vulnerability scanning

Exposure to serverless architecture (e.g., AWS Lambda)

Knowledge of GitOps, ArgoCD, or FluxCD

Certification in AWS (e.g., AWS Certified DevOps Engineer) is a big plus

🎁 What We Offer
Market-competitive salary

Hybrid work model (flexible days)

Annual performance bonuses

Medical coverage for self and family

Certifications & learning support

Modern office environment and a DevOps-first culture

📬 Apply Now
Send your CV and relevant project links to jobs@cloudnest.pk with subject line: DevOps Engineer – Islamabad.
Deadline to apply: June 15, 2025
